When I try to load a png file into a Texture2D, I get a NullReferenceException thrown here (Texture2D.DirectX.cs : PlatformFromStream() : around line 172):

```
Threading.BlockOnUIThread(() =>
{
    BitmapImage bitmapImage = new BitmapImage();
    bitmapImage.SetSource(stream);
    bitmap = new WriteableBitmap(bitmapImage);
});

ConvertToABGR(bitmap.PixelHeight, bitmap.PixelWidth, bitmap.Pixels); // NullReferenceException
```

It seems that `bitmap` is null - or rather, is never assigned with anything. I have tried using EventWaitHandle with it, but it leads to hanging indefinitely. I also tried removing the action call altogether, but this leads to UnauthorizedAccessException (BitmapImage cannot be accessed in non-UI threads, AFAIK).

Is there any way to actually create Texture2D objects at the moment?

